title: Gustave Caillebotte Paris Street; Rainy Day Umbrella and Tote
description:
Tote and Umbrella developed from Gustave Caillebotte Paris Street; Rainy Day, 1877, from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Step out in style with this tote and umbrella. Caillebotte’s masterpiece captured a vast, stark modernity, complete with life-size figures strolling in the foreground and wearing the latest fashions.

  • Umbrella
  • Dimensions: Closed- 11 x 2 in.  Open – 36 in.
  • Materials: Polyester
  • Auto open, close.
  • Storage sleeve for umbrella included
  • Tote
  • Dimensions: 16.5 x 12 x 4 in. Strap drop 11in.
  • Materials: Polycanvas, microfiber lining.
  • Zippered closure, internal zipper pocket.
